==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dasymeter
<hw>Da*sym"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>dasy`s</grk> rough, thick + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument for testing the density of
gases, consisting of a thin glass globe, which is weighed in the gas or
gases, and then in an atmosphere of known density.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

